data.message:
Expose xacro's message(), warning(), error(), and fatal() functions

Sometimes it is useful to generate some non-XML output, e.g.
for debugging or to inform about deprecated macros or parameters.

```
${xacro.message('message', 'text', 2, 3.14, color=32)}
${xacro.warning('warning')}
${xacro.error('error')}
${xacro.fatal('fatal')}
```
